cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CL 

This paper is about semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a new technique that involves learning, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper mentions auto-piloting, which is a robotics application, indicating that it could also be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper discusses semantic boundaries, which is a natural language processing concept, suggesting that it could also be classified under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
